  <title>GstPbutils.Discoverer</title>
  
  <synopsis><code>
const GstPbutils = imports.gi.GstPbutils;

let discoverer = new GstPbutils.Discoverer({
    <link xref='GstPbutils.Discoverer-timeout'>timeout</link>: value,
});
  </code></synopsis>

  
    <p>The <link xref="GstPbutils.Discoverer"/> is a utility object which allows to get as much
information as possible from one or many URIs.</p><p>It provides two APIs, allowing usage in blocking or non-blocking mode.</p><p>The blocking mode just requires calling <link xref="GstPbutils.discover_uri"/>
with the URI one wishes to discover.</p><p>The non-blocking mode requires a running <link xref="GLib.MainLoop"/> in the default
<link xref="GLib.MainContext"/>, where one connects to the various signals, appends the
URIs to be processed (through <link xref="GstPbutils.discover_uri_async"/>) and then
asks for the discovery to begin (through <link xref="GstPbutils.start"/>).</p><p>All the information is returned in a <link xref="GstPbutils.DiscovererInfo"/> structure.</p>
  
  
  
  
